cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.CV 

This paper deals with generating adversarial examples for text classifiers, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses deep learning models and reinforcement learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence research, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also deals with security and vulnerability of models, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper uses techniques for generating adversarial examples, which could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
